page.title: 02ANIMALS AND BIRDS ON WHALSAY
page.content:
There are a few wild animals on Whalsay.Here are the animals that do live here. Hedgehogs,Rats,Mice,Rabbits,Seals, Otters. There are many birds.Here are some of them.We have put the English names in brackets after Shetland names.
Tirricks (Terns), Shalders (Oyster Catchers), Maalies (Fulmar),Kittiwake, Black Back Gulls,Common Gull, Tammie Norries (Puffins), Sandiloo(Ringed plovers), Robins,Artic Skua, Bonxie (Great Skua), Swans,Whaap(Curlew), Geese,Dunters(Eider ducks), Rain Geese (Divers),Wrens,Herring Gull, Starlings, Black Headed Gull, Larks, Scarf(Shag),Sparrows. Some of these birds are resident but some are just visitors.
